    "en": {
      "title": "A solar-powered tricycle developed by a 10th year student in Kilinochchi",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A student studying at Kilinochchi Madhyamaha Vidyalaya has created a three-wheeled vehicle that can run on solar panels without fuel.",
        "According to the student, this three-wheeler designed by Sundaralingam Pranavan, who is studying in the 10th year, has now been able to drive successfully.",
        "The Sundaralingam student said that it took about 06 months to create this three-wheeler using solar panels that can run at a maximum speed of 50 kilometers per hour. Commenting on that, the student said,",
        "\"Because of the corona virus, we have no way to go to school. Even though I studied online, it was boring to sit at home most of the day. There is no way to play with friends due to the risk of corona. So I spent most of the day with my grandfather. He is a good mechanic, so when I told my grandfather about the design of a three-wheeler using solar panels, he helped me.",
        "So, with the help of my grandfather, I made this solar cell powered three wheeler for the last 6 months. I am very happy that my creation has been successful. This will also be a good solution to the country's fuel problem.\""
      ],
